Navigate to other release versions of Doxee Platform Process Designer

[6.6](https://docs.doxee.com/docs/en/process-designer-6-6)

[6.7](https://docs.doxee.com/docs/en/process-designer-6-7)

Process Designer is a support tool for Process Engine. It provides a graphical interface for creating, editing and testing process definitions which can be executed with Process Engine. Process Designer covers all features a process in an Infinica Process Definition (IPD) file can include, removing the necessity of manually writing XML code. Combining it with an instance of Process Engine is an optional feature, enabling Process Designer to load certain information dynamically and allowing the user to execute a process directly from the design workbench, providing useful feedback to the user.

This document includes an installation guide, a quick-start guide providing a short overview of the basic features and a detailed description of the complete functionality. It does not explain any details about Process Engine or the IPD format itself. A basic knowledge about these topics is required in order to be able to understand the concepts behind the processes which can be edited with Process Designer. To learn more about them, please consult the Process Engine Documentation.

The main window in Process Designer is called workbench and consists of a menu bar and a toolbar at the top, an editor and a variable number of optional views. The editor is described in [Editor](/doxee-platform/docs/6-6-process-designer-process-designer-user-guide-editor), the views are listed and explained in [Views](/doxee-platform/docs/6-6-process-designer-process-designer-user-guide-views) and all the functionalities available via the menu or the toolbar are summarized in [Actions](/doxee-platform/docs/6-6-process-designer-process-designer-user-guide-actions).
